=head1 DESCRIPTION

The level of detail included in each aspect of your DataSync task
report
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/datasync/latest/userguide/task-reports.html).

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Deleted => L<Paws::Datasync::ReportOverride>

Specifies the level of reporting for the files, objects, and
directories that DataSync attempted to delete in your destination
location. This only applies if you configure your task
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/datasync/latest/userguide/configure-metadata.html)
to delete data in the destination that isn't in the source.


=head2 Skipped => L<Paws::Datasync::ReportOverride>

Specifies the level of reporting for the files, objects, and
directories that DataSync attempted to skip during your transfer.


=head2 Transferred => L<Paws::Datasync::ReportOverride>

Specifies the level of reporting for the files, objects, and
directories that DataSync attempted to transfer.


=head2 Verified => L<Paws::Datasync::ReportOverride>

Specifies the level of reporting for the files, objects, and
directories that DataSync attempted to verify at the end of your
transfer.



